1
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:10,277
(singing in foreign language)

2
00:00:23,557 --> 00:00:26,159
(choir singing)

3
00:01:07,768 --> 00:01:09,670
(speaking Latin)

4
00:01:09,670 --> 00:01:12,272
(choir continues)

5
00:01:17,477 --> 00:01:18,845
(speaking Latin)

6
00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:30,090
(speaking Latin)

7
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:34,661
(choir continues)

8
00:02:05,659 --> 00:02:08,261
Partition.

9
00:02:08,261 --> 00:02:09,329
Now that the British are leaving

10
00:02:09,329 --> 00:02:11,331
India, the subcontinent will be

11
00:02:11,331 --> 00:02:13,967
divided into two countries--

12
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:16,269
India, where the Hindus are

13
00:02:16,269 --> 00:02:19,272
majority, and East and West

14
00:02:19,272 --> 00:02:21,608
Pakistan, where Muslims will be

15
00:02:21,608 --> 00:02:22,943
the rulers.

16
00:02:22,943 --> 00:02:24,678
Yes, Sunita?

17
00:02:24,678 --> 00:02:25,846
Is this something the British

18
00:02:25,846 --> 00:02:27,848
want, or do we Indians want it?

19
00:02:27,848 --> 00:02:29,950
Oh...

20
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:31,585
Opinions are divided on all

21
00:02:31,585 --> 00:02:32,919
sides.

22
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:34,588
Mahatma Gandhi is against

23
00:02:34,588 --> 00:02:36,390
partition, but many people who

24
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:38,592
follow him are all for it.

25
00:02:38,592 --> 00:02:40,927
They believe that Hindus and

26
00:02:40,927 --> 00:02:42,262
Muslims cannot live together

27
00:02:42,262 --> 00:02:44,398
in free country.

28
00:02:44,398 --> 00:02:45,632
Alice?

29
00:02:45,632 --> 00:02:46,566
What do you think,

30
00:02:46,566 --> 00:02:48,702
Sister Teresa?

31
00:02:48,702 --> 00:02:50,804
There was a reason God asked

32
00:02:50,804 --> 00:02:52,839
me to join his church.

33
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:54,574
He knows I have no head

34
00:02:54,574 --> 00:02:55,842
for politics.

35
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:56,710
(laughter, bell rings)

36
00:02:56,710 --> 00:02:58,412
Oh, 4:00, girls.

37
00:02:58,412 --> 00:02:59,713
That's all for today.

38
00:02:59,713 --> 00:03:01,915
We'll be late for Vespers.

39
00:03:05,385 --> 00:03:06,453
What do you mean there is

40
00:03:06,453 --> 00:03:07,654
no food?

41
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:08,822
Headmistress, we haven't had

42
00:03:08,822 --> 00:03:11,191
any deliveries for two weeks.

43
00:03:12,426 --> 00:03:13,927
Hadi, there is nothing

44
00:03:13,927 --> 00:03:16,396
to cook, at all?

45
00:03:16,396 --> 00:03:17,397
No.

46
00:03:17,397 --> 00:03:18,698
But we have 200 girls

47
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:19,733
to feed.

48
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:20,834
There are riots in the

49
00:03:20,834 --> 00:03:21,902
street, ma'am.

50
00:03:21,902 --> 00:03:23,303
No one can go out.

51
00:03:23,303 --> 00:03:24,704
This is not a safe area for us

52
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:25,639
to live in.

53
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:26,640
It's right in between the Hindus

54
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,607
and the Muslims.

55
00:03:27,607 --> 00:03:30,577
Sister Gabriella...

56
00:03:30,577 --> 00:03:31,645
if the mountain don't come

57
00:03:31,645 --> 00:03:32,746
to Mohammed...

58
00:03:34,614 --> 00:03:35,882
Mr. Pradesh's warehouse

59
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:37,717
should be down here.

60
00:03:37,717 --> 00:03:39,319
This is it.

61
00:03:44,357 --> 00:03:45,992
Hello? Hello?

62
00:03:45,992 --> 00:03:47,527
Mr. Pradesh!

63
00:03:47,527 --> 00:03:48,695
Hello?

64
00:03:48,695 --> 00:03:51,498
(crowd shouting)

65
00:03:52,632 --> 00:03:54,234
Oh!

66
00:03:56,536 --> 00:03:58,305
(gasps)

67
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,541
(child cries)

68
00:04:04,010 --> 00:04:05,779
What brings two nuns out of

69
00:04:05,779 --> 00:04:07,481
cloisters at a time like this?

70
00:04:07,481 --> 00:04:08,482
An emergency.

71
00:04:08,482 --> 00:04:09,749
We are from Loreto Convent,

72
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:11,618
with 200 hungry girls to feed

73
00:04:11,618 --> 00:04:12,552
and no food.

74
00:04:12,552 --> 00:04:13,553
Well, there's only meat for

75
00:04:13,553 --> 00:04:14,454
vultures out here.

76
00:04:14,454 --> 00:04:15,956
No, I can't let those girls

77
00:04:15,956 --> 00:04:16,923
go hungry.

78
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:18,758
Oh, come on, then. Douglas!

79
00:04:18,758 --> 00:04:20,060
I'm sure they won't miss a bag

80
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:22,395
or two.

81
00:04:22,395 --> 00:04:24,798
(crowd continues shouting)

82
00:04:28,068 --> 00:04:30,103
On board, ladies, on board.

83
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:31,638
Ah!

84
00:04:34,508 --> 00:04:35,675
This should keep your little

85
00:04:35,675 --> 00:04:37,711
lot fed till this mess is over.

86
00:04:37,711 --> 00:04:39,379
Are we stealing this?

87
00:04:39,379 --> 00:04:40,447
Requisition is the word.

88
00:04:40,447 --> 00:04:41,548
I'm sure your credit's good,

89
00:04:41,548 --> 00:04:42,482
Sister.

90
00:04:42,482 --> 00:04:45,051
Come on, lad.

91
00:04:45,051 --> 00:04:46,486
Come on!

92
00:04:54,661 --> 00:04:55,862
When you see what we had these

93
00:04:55,862 --> 00:04:56,830
last few days, you'll say to

94
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:57,898
yourself, "We've given them

95
00:04:57,898 --> 00:04:59,065
everything we can,

96
00:04:59,065 --> 00:05:00,066
so let 'em have their blasted

97
00:05:00,066 --> 00:05:01,701
independence."

98
00:05:01,701 --> 00:05:03,870
(car horn honking)

99
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:05,405
Get off!

100
00:05:05,405 --> 00:05:07,107
Back off, make way!

101
00:05:07,107 --> 00:05:09,075
(crowd continues shouting)

102
00:05:09,075 --> 00:05:10,577
Get back!

103
00:05:10,577 --> 00:05:11,578
Get off!

104
00:05:11,578 --> 00:05:13,313
Get out of the way!

105
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:17,117
Please, Sahib, help us!

106
00:05:17,117 --> 00:05:19,152
Please help, Sahib!

107
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:21,922
Rice for me and for my child!

108
00:05:21,922 --> 00:05:23,690
Pay no attention, Sister.

109
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:24,691
The war has caused these people

110
00:05:24,691 --> 00:05:25,725
to be put through the worst

111
00:05:25,725 --> 00:05:26,893
famine in Indian history.

112
00:05:26,893 --> 00:05:27,961
They've been starving ever

113
00:05:27,961 --> 00:05:29,129
since.

114
00:05:29,129 --> 00:05:30,430
Get off!

115
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:31,731
Ride, man, ride!

116
00:05:31,731 --> 00:05:34,334
(crowd continues shouting)

117
00:05:38,638 --> 00:05:40,674
Go, go, go!

118
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:41,675
You're gonna get yourselves

119
00:05:41,675 --> 00:05:43,376
killed!

120
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,982
Come on, Douglas, open the gate.

121
00:05:51,885 --> 00:05:53,820
Now, move it! Go!

122
00:06:02,596 --> 00:06:03,964
What's going on?

123
00:06:03,964 --> 00:06:05,765
Mother, we have food.

124
00:06:05,765 --> 00:06:06,666
We have food!

125
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:07,834
Oh, glory be to God!

126
00:06:07,834 --> 00:06:09,869
Cook! Food!

127
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:12,472
(crowd shouting)

128
00:06:22,616 --> 00:06:25,018
(girls screaming)

129
00:06:28,121 --> 00:06:29,756
(gasps)

130
00:06:30,857 --> 00:06:32,392
Ashad!

131
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:34,961
To infirmary.

132
00:06:34,961 --> 00:06:37,230
Yes, yes, Sister.

133
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,765
He's bleeding-- I don't know

134
00:06:38,765 --> 00:06:41,701
how to help.

135
00:06:41,701 --> 00:06:43,803
Oh, Lord.

136
00:06:45,672 --> 00:06:46,906
Right.

137
00:06:46,906 --> 00:06:48,575
Put pressure on his wounds.

138
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:51,011
He's lost a lot of blood.

139
00:06:51,011 --> 00:06:52,545
No, no.

140
00:06:52,545 --> 00:06:53,813
You must keep up the pressure.

141
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:55,949
We've got to stop the bleeding.

142
00:06:55,949 --> 00:06:57,684
Can you do it?

143
00:06:57,684 --> 00:06:58,752
Sister, I am geography

144
00:06:58,752 --> 00:07:00,120
teacher.

145
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:04,791
(sighs)

146
00:07:11,031 --> 00:07:12,966
Sister Teresa,

147
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:15,201
I thought I'd find you here.

148
00:07:15,201 --> 00:07:17,504
May I speak with you?

149
00:07:21,007 --> 00:07:22,642
Sister Gabriella told me how

150
00:07:22,642 --> 00:07:24,044
distressing it was to go

151
00:07:24,044 --> 00:07:26,846
outside.

152
00:07:26,846 --> 00:07:28,114
I'm so ashamed.

153
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:29,282
Ashamed?

154
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:30,283
But you went out for a good

155
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,085
reason.

156
00:07:32,085 --> 00:07:33,687
I saw the starving children

157
00:07:33,687 --> 00:07:35,855
of God out there, Father.

158
00:07:35,855 --> 00:07:37,657
I did nothing to help.

159
00:07:37,657 --> 00:07:38,925
You were bringing food for

160
00:07:38,925 --> 00:07:41,094
our girls.

161
00:07:41,094 --> 00:07:42,095
There were girls out there

162
00:07:42,095 --> 00:07:44,197
too, Father.

163
00:07:44,197 --> 00:07:45,899
Hungrier than ours.

164
00:07:45,899 --> 00:07:47,600
But our first duty is to our

165
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,636
school and our convent, Sister,

166
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:51,838
surely.

167
00:07:51,838 --> 00:07:53,807
How can that be?

168
00:07:53,807 --> 00:07:55,575
How can God wish me to be

169
00:07:55,575 --> 00:07:56,743
concerned only about the girls

170
00:07:56,743 --> 00:07:58,211
in here?

171
00:07:58,211 --> 00:07:59,846
Surely, he cares as much about

172
00:07:59,846 --> 00:08:00,947
the people living outside

173
00:08:00,947 --> 00:08:03,683
these walls?

174
00:08:03,683 --> 00:08:04,918
We're all under strain

175
00:08:04,918 --> 00:08:07,220
right now, Sister.

176
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:09,022
I spoke with Mother Superior.

177
00:08:09,022 --> 00:08:10,623
We both feel you should go on

178
00:08:10,623 --> 00:08:12,258
retreat sooner than planned.

179
00:08:12,258 --> 00:08:14,127
You need time to think things

180
00:08:14,127 --> 00:08:15,228
through--

181
00:08:15,228 --> 00:08:17,330
to rediscover the joy

182
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:19,599
in your work.

183
00:08:21,968 --> 00:08:24,604
Father Verru was right.

184
00:08:24,604 --> 00:08:25,972
But I could not forget what I

185
00:08:25,972 --> 00:08:27,741
had seen outside.

186
00:08:27,741 --> 00:08:29,576
And I knew I had to do something

187
00:08:29,576 --> 00:08:30,844
to make life better for the

188
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:32,946
poor.

189
00:08:32,946 --> 00:08:34,748
Mary can't sleep, Sister.

190
00:08:34,748 --> 00:08:35,715
She says she's having

191
00:08:35,715 --> 00:08:37,617
nightmares.

192
00:08:37,617 --> 00:08:39,652
Mary, Mary.

193
00:08:41,321 --> 00:08:43,189
Hey.

194
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:49,095
When I was nine years old,

195
00:08:49,095 --> 00:08:51,998
my father died.

196
00:08:51,998 --> 00:08:54,100
In my own country, Albania,

197
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,603
where I was born, there was a

198
00:08:56,603 --> 00:08:58,738
lot of political strife.

199
00:08:58,738 --> 00:09:01,007
For many years, I couldn't

200
00:09:01,007 --> 00:09:03,343
understand what happened,

201
00:09:03,343 --> 00:09:06,980
why my father didn't come home.

202
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:08,681
And I used to recite a poem to

203
00:09:08,681 --> 00:09:11,284
myself over and over.

204
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:18,091
"His red heart beat with love

205
00:09:18,091 --> 00:09:21,761
for child, wife, and country,

206
00:09:21,761 --> 00:09:24,764
and then burst into bloom,

207
00:09:24,764 --> 00:09:29,002
like crimson rose dropped

208
00:09:29,002 --> 00:09:32,839
on crumpled shirt."

209
00:09:32,839 --> 00:09:35,275
This poem is about believing in

210
00:09:35,275 --> 00:09:38,711
love, Mary, even when everything

211
00:09:38,711 --> 00:09:40,780
you see around you is hatred

212
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:42,982
and destruction.

213
00:09:42,982 --> 00:09:44,884
To bed.

214
00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:50,323
Mary?

215
00:09:50,323 --> 00:09:52,392
Tomorrow, I think you have a

216
00:09:52,392 --> 00:09:54,761
poem to write,

217
00:09:54,761 --> 00:09:55,962
just like I did when I was

218
00:09:55,962 --> 00:09:57,363
nine years old and when

219
00:09:57,363 --> 00:09:59,199
my father died.

220
00:10:02,202 --> 00:10:04,137
Goodnight, girls, God bless you.

221
00:10:04,137 --> 00:10:07,307
(girls) Goodnight, Sister.

222
00:10:07,307 --> 00:10:10,143
Sister?

223
00:10:10,143 --> 00:10:12,278
I-- some of the older girls,

224
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,847
they say we shouldn't take care

225
00:10:13,847 --> 00:10:16,015
of the injured Muslims.

226
00:10:16,015 --> 00:10:17,183
They say they are to blame for

227
00:10:17,183 --> 00:10:19,219
the violence.

228
00:10:19,219 --> 00:10:20,253
We take in whoever needs

229
00:10:20,253 --> 00:10:22,188
our help, Maria.

230
00:10:22,188 --> 00:10:24,357
Hindus, Muslims-- makes no

231
00:10:24,357 --> 00:10:26,259
difference to God.

232
00:10:31,931 --> 00:10:34,767
(train whistle blowing)

233
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:36,703
Darjeeling!

234
00:10:36,703 --> 00:10:39,439
Darjeeling train, all aboard!

235
00:10:39,439 --> 00:10:42,942
All aboard, Darjeeling train!

236
00:10:42,942 --> 00:10:44,911
All aboard!

237
00:10:46,212 --> 00:10:48,982
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty,

238
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:50,950
I'm thirsty.

239
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:55,288
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty.

240
00:10:55,288 --> 00:10:58,091
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty, ma'am.

241
00:10:58,091 --> 00:11:00,360
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty,

242
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,862
I'm thirsty, ma'am.

243
00:11:02,862 --> 00:11:04,764
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty--

244
00:11:04,764 --> 00:11:06,366
Sister Teresa, come on,

245
00:11:06,366 --> 00:11:09,035
we're leaving.

246
00:11:09,035 --> 00:11:11,804
Thirsty, I'm thirsty.

247
00:11:11,804 --> 00:11:13,973
I'm thirsty.

248
00:11:13,973 --> 00:11:15,875
(groans)

249
00:11:19,312 --> 00:11:21,681
I'm thirsty, ma'am, I'm thirsty.

250
00:11:23,883 --> 00:11:25,251
Please, Sister.

251
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:27,186
I'm thirsty.

252
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:30,023
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty.

253
00:11:35,461 --> 00:11:38,064
(train whistle blowing)

254
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:47,240
So, what can I bring you

255
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,875
today, sir?

256
00:11:56,282 --> 00:11:58,418
(sighs)

257
00:11:58,418 --> 00:11:59,786
Look at it.

258
00:11:59,786 --> 00:12:01,821
Breathtaking, isn't it?

259
00:12:01,821 --> 00:12:02,989
I so look forward to these

260
00:12:02,989 --> 00:12:04,857
retreats.

261
00:12:04,857 --> 00:12:06,292
I can almost taste the mountain

262
00:12:06,292 --> 00:12:08,394
spring water right now.

263
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:11,431
It's so fresh-- and the fruit!

264
00:12:11,431 --> 00:12:13,199
It always tastes much better

265
00:12:13,199 --> 00:12:14,901
up there.

266
00:12:19,005 --> 00:12:22,108
(flute playing)

267
00:12:22,108 --> 00:12:24,911
(train whistle blowing)

268
00:12:28,915 --> 00:12:31,317
(overlapping chatter)

269
00:12:36,122 --> 00:12:37,156
The more time I spent

270
00:12:37,156 --> 00:12:39,392
outside, the more I became aware

271
00:12:39,392 --> 00:12:40,927
of the privileges that were

272
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:42,528
being granted to me

273
00:12:42,528 --> 00:12:44,364
but denied to others.

274
00:12:44,364 --> 00:12:45,598
Why?

275
00:12:45,598 --> 00:12:47,166
Why should I be treated any

276
00:12:47,166 --> 00:12:48,534
differently?

277
00:12:48,534 --> 00:12:50,470
We are all children of God.

278
00:12:53,139 --> 00:12:54,374
Sister?

279
00:12:54,374 --> 00:12:55,308
Come-- your friend, come.

280
00:12:55,308 --> 00:12:56,376
What-- what is it?

281
00:12:56,376 --> 00:12:58,244
She's gone into third class.

282
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:07,420
(gasps) Sister Teresa!

283
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:09,489
What on Earth are you doing?

284
00:13:13,326 --> 00:13:14,961
It's another world, isn't it?

285
00:13:14,961 --> 00:13:16,863
It's completely unacceptable

286
00:13:16,863 --> 00:13:18,297
behavior.

287
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:20,800
I mean, what will people think?

288
00:13:24,037 --> 00:13:25,304
I wish I had time to find

289
00:13:25,304 --> 00:13:26,973
out.

290
00:13:33,946 --> 00:13:37,016
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty.

291
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:39,552
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty,

292
00:13:39,552 --> 00:13:42,288
thirsty, I'm thirsty...

293
00:13:51,464 --> 00:13:53,132
Welcome back.

294
00:13:53,132 --> 00:13:55,168
I understand you were very quiet

295
00:13:55,168 --> 00:13:58,271
on retreat, very withdrawn.

296
00:13:58,271 --> 00:13:59,405
I'm sorry, Father.

297
00:13:59,405 --> 00:14:00,473
Oh, it's not to apologize

298
00:14:00,473 --> 00:14:01,974
for.

299
00:14:01,974 --> 00:14:03,376
I understand you were deep in

300
00:14:03,376 --> 00:14:04,644
your thoughts.

301
00:14:04,644 --> 00:14:06,579
And you do seem more rested.

302
00:14:06,579 --> 00:14:08,314
Yes, Father.

303
00:14:08,314 --> 00:14:10,650
I am resolved.

304
00:14:10,650 --> 00:14:12,285
In fact, God himself told me

305
00:14:12,285 --> 00:14:13,920
what I must do.

306
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:16,089
God lets us know him by our

307
00:14:16,089 --> 00:14:17,090
own feelings.

308
00:14:17,090 --> 00:14:18,691
He spoke to me.

309
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:20,093
He spoke to me through the voice

310
00:14:20,093 --> 00:14:21,094
of a sick beggar.

311
00:14:21,094 --> 00:14:21,961
Sister--

312
00:14:21,961 --> 00:14:23,029
I heard him clearly.

313
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:23,963
Sister, you realize

314
00:14:23,963 --> 00:14:24,664
what you're--

315
00:14:24,664 --> 00:14:26,432
He said, "I am thirsty,"

316
00:14:26,432 --> 00:14:27,366
Father.

317
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:29,135
You think you heard the voice

318
00:14:29,135 --> 00:14:30,436
of God?

319
00:14:30,436 --> 00:14:32,271
Same way I heard him when he

320
00:14:32,271 --> 00:14:33,473
called me to his church, even

321
00:14:33,473 --> 00:14:36,709
though I was too young, only 13.

322
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:39,378
Now, he has called me again.

323
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:40,513
He wants me to follow him

324
00:14:40,513 --> 00:14:42,515
into the slums, to help the

325
00:14:42,515 --> 00:14:44,217
poorest of the poor.

326
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:45,485
But you're a cloistered nun,

327
00:14:45,485 --> 00:14:47,019
you can't go outside.

328
00:14:47,019 --> 00:14:49,722
Father, it is a call.

329
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:51,991
It's a call within the call.

330
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:54,961
Do you remember what Mahatma

331
00:14:54,961 --> 00:14:56,062
Gandhi told the Christians in

332
00:14:56,062 --> 00:14:57,396
India?

333
00:14:57,396 --> 00:15:00,266
He said, "If you want to help,

334
00:15:00,266 --> 00:15:03,402
go to the people as one of them.

335
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:05,037
Work among them."

336
00:15:05,037 --> 00:15:06,639
How can we do that from behind

337
00:15:06,639 --> 00:15:08,040
these gated walls?

338
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,242
You no longer want to be

339
00:15:09,242 --> 00:15:10,209
a nun?

340
00:15:10,209 --> 00:15:11,410
Heaven forbid, Father,

341
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:14,247
the church is my life.

342
00:15:14,247 --> 00:15:15,648
No, I only want permission

343
00:15:15,648 --> 00:15:17,283
to work outside.

344
00:15:25,458 --> 00:15:26,592
I've heard of nuns suffering

345
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:28,261
delusions as a result of heat

346
00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:32,031
stroke, but this takes the cake.

347
00:15:32,031 --> 00:15:33,199
We've all been affected by

348
00:15:33,199 --> 00:15:34,567
the troubles.

349
00:15:34,567 --> 00:15:36,035
And it could be that Sister

350
00:15:36,035 --> 00:15:38,237
Teresa is struggling to reaffirm

351
00:15:38,237 --> 00:15:39,572
her faith.

352
00:15:39,572 --> 00:15:41,541
But she believes God has called

353
00:15:41,541 --> 00:15:43,776
her to follow him into the slum.

354
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:45,378
Well?

355
00:15:45,378 --> 00:15:47,346
I believe that Sister Teresa

356
00:15:47,346 --> 00:15:49,315
is sincere.

357
00:15:49,315 --> 00:15:51,083
She just hasn't considered

358
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:52,285
the implications.

359
00:15:52,285 --> 00:15:53,486
Which are?

360
00:15:53,486 --> 00:15:55,021
It'll upset the entire

361
00:15:55,021 --> 00:15:57,056
convent if a nun of Sister

362
00:15:57,056 --> 00:15:58,591
Teresa's experience gives up

363
00:15:58,591 --> 00:16:00,159
everything and leaves.

364
00:16:00,159 --> 00:16:01,360
She wants to apply for

365
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:04,063
exclaustration, Mother Superior.

366
00:16:04,063 --> 00:16:05,264
This would allow her to remain

367
00:16:05,264 --> 00:16:06,799
in the Loreto Order and live

368
00:16:06,799 --> 00:16:08,467
by her vows.

369
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:10,303
All she's asking for is

370
00:16:10,303 --> 00:16:11,504
permission to work outside

371
00:16:11,504 --> 00:16:12,438
the walls.

372
00:16:12,438 --> 00:16:14,507
That's the other problem.

373
00:16:14,507 --> 00:16:16,642
The Loreto Order has always

374
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:18,277
been cloistered.

375
00:16:18,277 --> 00:16:19,745
And now a nun comes along and

376
00:16:19,745 --> 00:16:22,782
says she heard the voice of God,

377
00:16:22,782 --> 00:16:24,717
in a tunnel!

378
00:16:24,717 --> 00:16:26,285
But she makes a compelling

379
00:16:26,285 --> 00:16:27,687
argument.

380
00:16:27,687 --> 00:16:28,754
She says that in the face of

381
00:16:28,754 --> 00:16:30,690
every suffering man, woman

382
00:16:30,690 --> 00:16:33,226
and child in India, we can find

383
00:16:33,226 --> 00:16:35,228
the face of Jesus Christ.

384
00:16:35,228 --> 00:16:37,363
She calls it God's distressing

385
00:16:37,363 --> 00:16:38,364
disguise.

386
00:16:38,364 --> 00:16:39,832
Heaven forbid one of the

387
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:42,201
children hears that the

388
00:16:42,201 --> 00:16:45,338
headmistress is hearing voices

389
00:16:45,338 --> 00:16:46,606
and seeing visions.

390
00:16:46,606 --> 00:16:47,707
I think it's clear this

391
00:16:47,707 --> 00:16:49,208
matter should remain strictly

392
00:16:49,208 --> 00:16:50,176
confidential.

393
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:51,477
Of course, but what are we

394
00:16:51,477 --> 00:16:53,412
to tell Sister Teresa?

395
00:16:53,412 --> 00:16:54,447
Tell her nothing.

396
00:16:54,447 --> 00:16:55,581
But Your Grace--

397
00:16:55,581 --> 00:16:56,682
This isn't the first time

398
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:58,251
a nun has asked for permission

399
00:16:58,251 --> 00:17:00,753
to leave the cloister.

400
00:17:00,753 --> 00:17:02,755
Last time, I advised the

401
00:17:02,755 --> 00:17:05,291
applicant to wait a year.

402
00:17:05,291 --> 00:17:07,660
12 months later, she sat in that

403
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:10,696
chair and thanked me for not

404
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,632
taking her request seriously.

405
00:17:12,632 --> 00:17:14,834
Sister Teresa, Your Grace,

406
00:17:14,834 --> 00:17:17,169
she's never not serious.

407
00:17:17,169 --> 00:17:18,437
Tell her to write a letter to

408
00:17:18,437 --> 00:17:21,574
me in a year's time.

409
00:17:21,574 --> 00:17:23,476
Until then,

410
00:17:23,476 --> 00:17:26,412
this matter is closed.

411
00:17:26,412 --> 00:17:28,814
♪♪

412
00:17:33,786 --> 00:17:36,822
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty,

413
00:17:36,822 --> 00:17:39,191
I'm thirsty, I'm thirsty,

414
00:17:39,191 --> 00:17:41,327
I'm thirsty...

415
00:17:46,432 --> 00:17:48,834
(choir singing)

416
00:18:07,286 --> 00:18:08,487
Commissioner?

417
00:18:08,487 --> 00:18:09,722
Harry Harper.

418
00:18:09,722 --> 00:18:10,890
We met the other night at the

419
00:18:10,890 --> 00:18:12,525
reception at Governor House.

420
00:18:12,525 --> 00:18:14,427
Ah, yes, yes.

421
00:18:14,427 --> 00:18:15,628
The American journalist

422
00:18:15,628 --> 00:18:16,662
hungry for a face-to-face

423
00:18:16,662 --> 00:18:17,630
with Mr. Gandhi.

424
00:18:17,630 --> 00:18:19,498
Yes, well, I'd like to report

425
00:18:19,498 --> 00:18:20,933
on India's transition to

426
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:22,802
independence fairly.

427
00:18:22,802 --> 00:18:24,170
People need to hear about

428
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:25,338
official ceremonies like this,

429
00:18:25,338 --> 00:18:26,639
but they also need to hear about

430
00:18:26,639 --> 00:18:28,240
Gandhi's presence in Calcutta

431
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,575
to protest the violence.

432
00:18:29,575 --> 00:18:31,444
(people applauding)

433
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:32,611
Do you really care about the

434
00:18:32,611 --> 00:18:34,880
Muslims and Hindus, Mr. Harper?

435
00:18:36,582 --> 00:18:37,583
Absolutely.

436
00:18:37,583 --> 00:18:39,251
(chuckles)

437
00:18:39,251 --> 00:18:41,654
(trumpet calling)

438
00:18:53,899 --> 00:18:56,502
(band playing)

439
00:19:19,658 --> 00:19:21,861
(applause)

440
00:19:24,964 --> 00:19:27,299
Now, the year is finished.

441
00:19:27,299 --> 00:19:28,734
The Archbishop has agreed to

442
00:19:28,734 --> 00:19:30,269
forward your letter to Rome,

443
00:19:30,269 --> 00:19:32,605
but only under one condition--

444
00:19:32,605 --> 00:19:34,707
that you apply for a decree of

445
00:19:34,707 --> 00:19:37,276
secularization.

446
00:19:37,276 --> 00:19:38,677
But that means I would have

447
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:39,712
to leave the order.

448
00:19:39,712 --> 00:19:41,480
It's the only way he will

449
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:43,482
consider your request.

450
00:19:43,482 --> 00:19:45,484
If you leave, you leave as a

451
00:19:45,484 --> 00:19:48,387
laywoman, not as a nun.

452
00:19:48,387 --> 00:19:50,356
But... I've lived as a nun

453
00:19:50,356 --> 00:19:51,857
for 17 years, I can't live

454
00:19:51,857 --> 00:19:54,326
any other way.

455
00:19:54,326 --> 00:19:55,394
Then you must give up the

456
00:19:55,394 --> 00:19:56,262
idea.

457
00:19:56,262 --> 00:19:58,297
I can't leave Loreto.

458
00:19:58,297 --> 00:20:00,866
Hello, there, Sister.

459
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:02,668
This is my family.

460
00:20:02,668 --> 00:20:04,670
It's too much of a risk.

461
00:20:04,670 --> 00:20:06,439
If your plan doesn't work out,

462
00:20:06,439 --> 00:20:07,740
you won't be able to come back

463
00:20:07,740 --> 00:20:09,542
here.

464
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:13,913
It's God's plan, Father,

465
00:20:13,913 --> 00:20:16,715
not mine.

466
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:18,951
I will rewrite the letter.

467
00:20:21,353 --> 00:20:23,055
A sad day, isn't it?

468
00:20:23,055 --> 00:20:24,056
No, not really.

469
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,858
It was good while it lasted.

470
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:30,496
So...

471
00:20:30,496 --> 00:20:31,831
you going back to England soon?

472
00:20:31,831 --> 00:20:33,332
No, not me, sir.

473
00:20:33,332 --> 00:20:34,467
I lost my wife and kids

474
00:20:34,467 --> 00:20:35,968
in the Blitz.

475
00:20:35,968 --> 00:20:37,870
Oh, well, I'm sorry.

476
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:40,005
Well, I've got my pension.

477
00:20:40,005 --> 00:20:41,307
I might get around to opening up

478
00:20:41,307 --> 00:20:42,842
a little hotel, gentlemen's

479
00:20:42,842 --> 00:20:43,876
club, that sort of thing.

480
00:20:43,876 --> 00:20:45,344
Uh-huh.

481
00:20:45,344 --> 00:20:47,413
Your first time in India?

482
00:20:47,413 --> 00:20:49,749
No, I was, um, born here

483
00:20:49,749 --> 00:20:50,783
actually.

484
00:20:50,783 --> 00:20:53,419
My parents moved to the States

485
00:20:53,419 --> 00:20:54,520
and settled there when I was

486
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:55,721
a kid.

487
00:20:55,721 --> 00:20:56,722
Oh, you work for the

488
00:20:56,722 --> 00:20:57,857
International Chronicle?

489
00:20:57,857 --> 00:20:59,091
Yep.

490
00:20:59,091 --> 00:21:00,426
And I have a feeling things

491
00:21:00,426 --> 00:21:01,460
aren't gonna stay quiet around

492
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:02,862
here for very long.

493
00:21:02,862 --> 00:21:03,896
You let me know if anything

494
00:21:03,896 --> 00:21:05,431
interesting happens in Calcutta?

495
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:06,999
Right you are, sir.

496
00:21:06,999 --> 00:21:08,501
(laughing)

497
00:21:08,501 --> 00:21:10,870
(overlapping chatter)

498
00:21:12,571 --> 00:21:14,607
Sister? Sister?

499
00:21:14,607 --> 00:21:15,975
You see that street?

500
00:21:15,975 --> 00:21:17,476
The families we visit during

501
00:21:17,476 --> 00:21:19,745
our Sodality outings live there.

502
00:21:19,745 --> 00:21:20,813
Would it be all right if we

503
00:21:20,813 --> 00:21:22,047
looked in on them?

504
00:21:22,047 --> 00:21:23,048
Oh, please?

505
00:21:23,048 --> 00:21:24,650
Then they can meet you.

506
00:21:24,650 --> 00:21:26,051
Well, if we all stick

507
00:21:26,051 --> 00:21:27,820
together, I suppose it'll be

508
00:21:27,820 --> 00:21:28,821
all right.

509
00:21:28,821 --> 00:21:29,855
You must not take more than

510
00:21:29,855 --> 00:21:30,923
half an hour.

511
00:21:30,923 --> 00:21:32,458
They will be worried at Loreto.

512
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:34,026
All right, girls.

513
00:21:34,026 --> 00:21:36,428
Stick together.

514
00:21:36,428 --> 00:21:38,831
(overlapping chatter)

515
00:21:59,885 --> 00:22:01,453
(gasps)

516
00:22:09,895 --> 00:22:11,030
This woman must be taken

517
00:22:11,030 --> 00:22:12,932
to hospital.

518
00:22:20,773 --> 00:22:24,143
What's wrong with you?

519
00:22:24,143 --> 00:22:26,145
She's dying.

520
00:22:26,145 --> 00:22:28,414
She needs care.

521
00:22:33,719 --> 00:22:34,920
(flies buzzing)

522
00:22:36,822 --> 00:22:39,959
(speaking foreign language)

523
00:22:39,959 --> 00:22:42,928
It's all right.

524
00:22:42,928 --> 00:22:44,797
We will help you.

525
00:22:47,499 --> 00:22:49,168
Our hospitals are so crowded,

526
00:22:49,168 --> 00:22:51,870
we just don't have any space.

527
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:53,005
It would be a waste to use

528
00:22:53,005 --> 00:22:54,773
valuable resources on a hopeless

529
00:22:54,773 --> 00:22:55,908
case.

530
00:22:55,908 --> 00:22:57,142
But she's a person.

531
00:22:57,142 --> 00:22:59,712
We can't do a thing for her.

532
00:22:59,712 --> 00:23:01,013
Like anyone else, she's one

533
00:23:01,013 --> 00:23:02,181
of God's children.

534
00:23:02,181 --> 00:23:03,883
I understand your feeling,

535
00:23:03,883 --> 00:23:05,184
Sister, but we just can't

536
00:23:05,184 --> 00:23:07,486
take her.

537
00:23:07,486 --> 00:23:08,887
What are we to do with her?

538
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:10,089
Try another hospital,

539
00:23:10,089 --> 00:23:11,724
I don't know!

540
00:23:13,792 --> 00:23:16,195
I want my cart back.

541
00:23:16,195 --> 00:23:17,730
But they won't take her.

542
00:23:17,730 --> 00:23:19,965
That's not my problem!

543
00:23:19,965 --> 00:23:22,801
(thunder cracking)

544
00:23:22,801 --> 00:23:24,937
Sister, take the girls

545
00:23:24,937 --> 00:23:26,005
back to Loreto.

546
00:23:26,005 --> 00:23:27,940
But what will you do?

547
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:29,675
I don't know.

548
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:32,611
Come on, girls, single file.

549
00:23:32,611 --> 00:23:33,979
You come with me.

550
00:23:33,979 --> 00:23:35,748
I take care of you.

551
00:23:35,748 --> 00:23:36,982
Come on.

552
00:23:36,982 --> 00:23:39,084
(woman groaning)

553
00:23:45,858 --> 00:23:47,760
You have to leave.

554
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:50,095
You're blocking the entryway.

555
00:23:52,798 --> 00:23:54,633
Don't worry now.

556
00:23:57,036 --> 00:23:59,238
All right, Ma?

557
00:23:59,238 --> 00:24:01,206
(rain falling)

558
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:05,911
Sister, the doctors have

559
00:24:05,911 --> 00:24:09,014
agreed to take her in.

560
00:24:09,014 --> 00:24:10,716
Bless you.

561
00:24:12,184 --> 00:24:15,054
Ma...

562
00:24:15,054 --> 00:24:16,255
You are doing a beautiful thing

563
00:24:16,255 --> 00:24:18,190
for God.

564
00:24:23,028 --> 00:24:25,631
(thunder roaring)

565
00:24:27,232 --> 00:24:29,001
My mother always said if you do

566
00:24:29,001 --> 00:24:30,736
something good, do it without

567
00:24:30,736 --> 00:24:32,538
big fuss.

568
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:37,543
Suddenly, I realized I was lost.

569
00:24:37,543 --> 00:24:38,644
Lost in the back streets of

570
00:24:38,644 --> 00:24:40,145
Calcutta.

571
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:41,313
Give me money.

572
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:42,748
Money, rupees for food.

573
00:24:42,748 --> 00:24:44,683
I don't have anything.

574
00:24:44,683 --> 00:24:45,951
No money.

575
00:24:45,951 --> 00:24:47,119
Why you in such a hurry?

576
00:24:47,119 --> 00:24:47,786
No.

577
00:24:47,786 --> 00:24:49,021
What are you hiding from us?

578
00:24:49,021 --> 00:24:50,622
No, no.

579
00:24:50,622 --> 00:24:52,825
Give me money. Money!

580
00:24:52,825 --> 00:24:55,227
Money!

581
00:24:55,227 --> 00:24:58,130
Can somebody help me?

582
00:24:58,130 --> 00:24:59,765
Please, can...

583
00:24:59,765 --> 00:25:01,300
(gasps)

584
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:02,701
Hari!

585
00:25:02,701 --> 00:25:04,203
Are you all right, Sister?

586
00:25:04,203 --> 00:25:04,870
Oh, yes.

587
00:25:04,870 --> 00:25:06,672
I didn't realize the outside

588
00:25:06,672 --> 00:25:09,208
world could be so confusing.

589
00:25:09,208 --> 00:25:11,176
You are very lucky, Sister,

590
00:25:11,176 --> 00:25:12,277
in this neighborhood.

591
00:25:12,277 --> 00:25:14,179
No, Hari.

592
00:25:14,179 --> 00:25:17,082
They're just very poor.

593
00:25:17,082 --> 00:25:19,785
I must get used to that.

594
00:25:19,785 --> 00:25:22,187
(organ playing)

595
00:25:24,723 --> 00:25:25,758
I have the reply to your

596
00:25:25,758 --> 00:25:26,625
letter.

597
00:25:26,625 --> 00:25:27,893
(gasps)

598
00:25:27,893 --> 00:25:29,161
If you like, I'll tear it up

599
00:25:29,161 --> 00:25:32,231
unread.

600
00:25:32,231 --> 00:25:34,199
If they've granted your request,

601
00:25:34,199 --> 00:25:36,101
this may be your last mass

602
00:25:36,101 --> 00:25:37,936
as a nun.

603
00:25:40,672 --> 00:25:42,741
Let me pray first, Father.

604
00:25:55,888 --> 00:25:58,557
Whatever God has decided for me.

605
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:06,832
Oh.

606
00:26:06,832 --> 00:26:08,700
Oh!

607
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:11,837
It is manifestly God's will.

608
00:26:11,837 --> 00:26:13,138
You've been granted the decree

609
00:26:13,138 --> 00:26:14,840
of exclaustration for a trial

610
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:16,809
period of one year.

611
00:26:16,809 --> 00:26:18,277
You can leave Loreto as a nun

612
00:26:18,277 --> 00:26:21,180
and remain in our order.

613
00:26:21,180 --> 00:26:23,048
How did this happen?

614
00:26:23,048 --> 00:26:24,850
I changed your request to

615
00:26:24,850 --> 00:26:26,919
secularization.

616
00:26:26,919 --> 00:26:28,187
It's as if...

617
00:26:28,187 --> 00:26:29,988
God knows what he wants.

618
00:26:29,988 --> 00:26:31,023
Yes!

619
00:26:31,023 --> 00:26:32,057
He knows.

620
00:26:32,057 --> 00:26:33,826
Yes!

621
00:26:37,162 --> 00:26:39,198
My friend Mr. Pillay has

622
00:26:39,198 --> 00:26:41,233
about the best saris.

623
00:26:41,233 --> 00:26:42,868
This is pure silk,

624
00:26:42,868 --> 00:26:44,369
worthy of a princess.

625
00:26:44,369 --> 00:26:46,104
The thread is real gold.

626
00:26:46,104 --> 00:26:47,840
Cotton, Hari.

627
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:50,843
I asked for a cheap cotton sari.

628
00:26:50,843 --> 00:26:52,678
I told him, but he said it's

629
00:26:52,678 --> 00:26:54,413
not fit for a European.

630
00:26:54,413 --> 00:26:58,350
Ah, how 'bout this, Sister?

631
00:26:58,350 --> 00:27:00,152
The cloth flows like wine.

632
00:27:00,152 --> 00:27:01,386
And probably costs the same

633
00:27:01,386 --> 00:27:02,454
too.

634
00:27:02,454 --> 00:27:05,724
Ah... what about this one?

635
00:27:05,724 --> 00:27:07,025
That one?

636
00:27:07,025 --> 00:27:08,260
That one he gave me very

637
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:09,761
reluctantly.

638
00:27:09,761 --> 00:27:12,231
It cost just a few rupees.

639
00:27:12,231 --> 00:27:14,066
This is the one.

640
00:27:17,135 --> 00:27:18,937
May the Father, Son, and Holy

641
00:27:18,937 --> 00:27:20,939
Ghost bless this habit and

642
00:27:20,939 --> 00:27:22,474
enable you to be faithful to

643
00:27:22,474 --> 00:27:23,876
your commitment for the rest of

644
00:27:23,876 --> 00:27:24,943
your life.

645
00:27:24,943 --> 00:27:25,944
In the name of the Father,

646
00:27:25,944 --> 00:27:27,479
the Son, and the Holy Ghost,

647
00:27:27,479 --> 00:27:29,147
Amen.

648
00:27:32,050 --> 00:27:33,452
His Grace, the Archbishop,

649
00:27:33,452 --> 00:27:34,853
would like you to keep a record

650
00:27:34,853 --> 00:27:36,755
of your activities.

651
00:27:36,755 --> 00:27:38,056
With all you hope to do for the

652
00:27:38,056 --> 00:27:39,358
poor in Calcutta, you'll need

653
00:27:39,358 --> 00:27:41,393
help of all kinds.

654
00:27:41,393 --> 00:27:42,394
Are you planning to meet

655
00:27:42,394 --> 00:27:43,495
with the governor?

656
00:27:43,495 --> 00:27:45,030
Oh, no, I won't do that.

657
00:27:45,030 --> 00:27:47,299
Then where will you begin?

658
00:27:47,299 --> 00:27:48,367
All I know is I must leave

659
00:27:48,367 --> 00:27:49,067
Loreto.

660
00:27:49,067 --> 00:27:51,937
After that, God will direct me.

661
00:27:51,937 --> 00:27:54,039
(bells tolling)

662
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:03,949
After dreaming of this day for

663
00:28:03,949 --> 00:28:06,151
two years, leaving Loreto

664
00:28:06,151 --> 00:28:07,452
Convent was the most difficult

665
00:28:07,452 --> 00:28:10,188
thing I had ever done--

666
00:28:10,188 --> 00:28:11,490
much more difficult than leaving

667
00:28:11,490 --> 00:28:13,759
my family.

668
00:28:13,759 --> 00:28:15,527
It was only my firm belief in

669
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:17,329
God's plan that gave me the

670
00:28:17,329 --> 00:28:18,497
courage to give up everything

671
00:28:18,497 --> 00:28:21,433
once again.

672
00:28:21,433 --> 00:28:23,302
He would not let me down.

673
00:28:36,181 --> 00:28:38,784
(overlapping chatter)

674
00:28:47,292 --> 00:28:49,328
(bell ringing)

675
00:28:53,899 --> 00:28:55,367
Mommy?

676
00:28:55,367 --> 00:28:56,535
You should go around

677
00:28:56,535 --> 00:28:57,469
the back.

678
00:28:57,469 --> 00:28:58,804
I will ask my cook to give you

679
00:28:58,804 --> 00:29:00,305
something to eat.

680
00:29:00,305 --> 00:29:03,408
I-- I'm looking for Mr. Goma.

681
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:04,543
Father Verru wrote to him

682
00:29:04,543 --> 00:29:05,410
about me.

683
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:07,079
I am Sister Teresa from

684
00:29:07,079 --> 00:29:07,946
Loreto Convent.

685
00:29:07,946 --> 00:29:09,848
(sighs)

686
00:29:11,350 --> 00:29:13,318
I'm so pleased!

687
00:29:13,318 --> 00:29:15,821
Forgive me, I was expecting

688
00:29:15,821 --> 00:29:16,888
a nun.

689
00:29:16,888 --> 00:29:18,357
Please come, Sister.

690
00:29:18,357 --> 00:29:19,925
My husband is waiting.

691
00:29:19,925 --> 00:29:21,426
Oh, thank you for your

692
00:29:21,426 --> 00:29:23,295
generosity.

693
00:29:23,295 --> 00:29:24,496
And the church wants you to

694
00:29:24,496 --> 00:29:26,832
work in a place like Moti Jihl?

695
00:29:26,832 --> 00:29:28,967
That's a huge risk, isn't it?

696
00:29:28,967 --> 00:29:30,268
Something I do willingly,

697
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:32,204
Mr. Goma.

698
00:29:32,204 --> 00:29:33,905
Father thought, as a member of

699
00:29:33,905 --> 00:29:35,874
his parish, perhaps you could

700
00:29:35,874 --> 00:29:37,509
suggest a place for me to stay

701
00:29:37,509 --> 00:29:40,078
not too far from Moti Jihl.

702
00:29:40,078 --> 00:29:42,114
As you can see, my own home

703
00:29:42,114 --> 00:29:43,248
is a humble place,

704
00:29:43,248 --> 00:29:45,317
and I have a large family.

705
00:29:45,317 --> 00:29:47,285
I'll have to think if, uh--

706
00:29:47,285 --> 00:29:49,554
Daddy, the two rooms upstairs

707
00:29:49,554 --> 00:29:51,890
are empty, and the attic.

708
00:29:51,890 --> 00:29:54,426
(clears throat)

709
00:29:54,426 --> 00:29:56,194
I suppose they are.

710
00:29:56,194 --> 00:29:57,529
But I doubt Sister will find

711
00:29:57,529 --> 00:29:59,231
them comfortable or--

712
00:29:59,231 --> 00:30:00,465
The simplest of rooms would

713
00:30:00,465 --> 00:30:02,000
be perfect.

714
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:03,235
I won't be in the way.

715
00:30:03,235 --> 00:30:04,503
I will be gone all day, only

716
00:30:04,503 --> 00:30:06,538
need a place to sleep at night.

717
00:30:18,250 --> 00:30:20,118
We have plenty of spare

718
00:30:20,118 --> 00:30:21,286
furniture.

719
00:30:21,286 --> 00:30:22,954
If you need anything, you can

720
00:30:22,954 --> 00:30:24,489
just ask, Sister.

721
00:30:24,489 --> 00:30:26,925
Thank you, you're very kind.

722
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:31,163
♪♪

723
00:30:45,977 --> 00:30:47,145
Mr. Goma.

724
00:30:47,145 --> 00:30:48,313
Oh, we have more chairs and

725
00:30:48,313 --> 00:30:49,915
tables you can borrow, Sister.

726
00:30:49,915 --> 00:30:51,950
The fewer possessions I have,

727
00:30:51,950 --> 00:30:54,186
the better.

728
00:31:00,559 --> 00:31:04,496
Nothing should distract me...

729
00:31:04,496 --> 00:31:06,965
from my work for the poor.

730
00:31:15,307 --> 00:31:17,909
(overlapping chatter)

731
00:31:27,652 --> 00:31:29,554
Sister, Sister, money!

732
00:31:29,554 --> 00:31:30,422
Hello.

733
00:31:30,422 --> 00:31:32,224
Sister, money.

734
00:31:32,224 --> 00:31:34,493
Money! Money! Money!

735
00:31:34,493 --> 00:31:36,161
Sister!

736
00:31:36,161 --> 00:31:38,396
Sister, money!

737
00:31:38,396 --> 00:31:40,999
(kids continue begging)

738
00:31:47,405 --> 00:31:48,440
I have no money.

739
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:50,976
No, I have-- I have no money!

740
00:31:50,976 --> 00:31:52,978
My lunch!

741
00:31:52,978 --> 00:31:55,380
(kids chattering)

742
00:32:00,652 --> 00:32:04,389
My name is Sister Teresa.

743
00:32:04,389 --> 00:32:05,557
I'm a daughter of the Christian

744
00:32:05,557 --> 00:32:06,725
Church.

745
00:32:06,725 --> 00:32:08,660
I have come to Moti Jihl

746
00:32:08,660 --> 00:32:11,696
to work with you.

747
00:32:11,696 --> 00:32:14,032
To try to improve your lives.

748
00:32:15,433 --> 00:32:18,236
But I need your help.

749
00:32:18,236 --> 00:32:20,071
I can't give you clothes,

750
00:32:20,071 --> 00:32:21,406
or food or money.

751
00:32:21,406 --> 00:32:24,543
I am as poor as you.

752
00:32:24,543 --> 00:32:27,012
But I can teach your children

753
00:32:27,012 --> 00:32:29,514
how to read.

754
00:32:29,514 --> 00:32:31,716
(woman screaming)

755
00:32:38,123 --> 00:32:40,625
(flies buzzing)

756
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:42,727
(screaming continues)

757
00:32:46,064 --> 00:32:48,400
(gasps) What are you doing?

758
00:32:50,435 --> 00:32:52,037
Leave her alone!

759
00:32:52,037 --> 00:32:53,705
(baby crying)

760
00:32:59,644 --> 00:33:02,080
(man singing in distance)

761
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:04,149
When I was a little girl in

762
00:33:04,149 --> 00:33:06,151
Skopia, Mother used to take me

763
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:08,386
to visit the poor.

764
00:33:08,386 --> 00:33:10,088
She taught us that it is our

765
00:33:10,088 --> 00:33:11,656
responsibility to help the less

766
00:33:11,656 --> 00:33:13,458
fortunate.

767
00:33:13,458 --> 00:33:14,826
Sometimes we would come to the

768
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:17,095
dinner table and find total

769
00:33:17,095 --> 00:33:18,496
strangers sitting down to share

770
00:33:18,496 --> 00:33:20,498
our meals.

771
00:33:20,498 --> 00:33:21,499
"Who are these people?"

772
00:33:21,499 --> 00:33:22,467
we would ask.

773
00:33:22,467 --> 00:33:23,468
She would say, "Distant

774
00:33:23,468 --> 00:33:25,070
kinsmen."

775
00:33:25,070 --> 00:33:26,504
But they were beggars and

776
00:33:26,504 --> 00:33:28,173
destitutes that my dear mama

777
00:33:28,173 --> 00:33:30,609
had brought in.

778
00:33:30,609 --> 00:33:33,478
But never did I see such poverty

779
00:33:33,478 --> 00:33:34,746
and suffering there

780
00:33:34,746 --> 00:33:38,650
as I see here.

781
00:33:38,650 --> 00:33:41,253
(overlapping chatter)

782
00:33:53,732 --> 00:33:55,267
Come!

783
00:33:59,404 --> 00:34:01,506
You want to eat my lunch again?

784
00:34:01,506 --> 00:34:03,208
Oh!

785
00:34:07,812 --> 00:34:11,349
Do you like to hear stories?

786
00:34:11,349 --> 00:34:13,118
I have a wonderful story

787
00:34:13,118 --> 00:34:14,119
I will tell you.

788
00:34:14,119 --> 00:34:17,355
Sit down.

789
00:34:17,355 --> 00:34:20,659
Once, a long time ago--

790
00:34:20,659 --> 00:34:22,694
I'm going to tell a story.

791
00:34:22,694 --> 00:34:24,229
A long, long time ago,

792
00:34:24,229 --> 00:34:26,631
there lived a handsome prince

793
00:34:26,631 --> 00:34:29,367
called Rama, and his beautiful

794
00:34:29,367 --> 00:34:31,836
wife called Sita.

795
00:34:31,836 --> 00:34:33,638
They lived in a big, beautiful

796
00:34:33,638 --> 00:34:36,641
palace in a beautiful country,

797
00:34:36,641 --> 00:34:39,678
but that was ruled by a very

798
00:34:39,678 --> 00:34:41,646
nasty king...

799
00:34:41,646 --> 00:34:43,448
And the king was slain by the

800
00:34:43,448 --> 00:34:45,250
brave prince, who rescued his

801
00:34:45,250 --> 00:34:46,818
princess, and they lived

802
00:34:46,818 --> 00:34:49,354
happily ever after.

803
00:34:49,354 --> 00:34:50,488
Another one!

804
00:34:50,488 --> 00:34:51,489
Tell us another one!

805
00:34:51,489 --> 00:34:52,590
You like stories?

806
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:53,625
Yes!

807
00:34:53,625 --> 00:34:54,626
You like stories?

808
00:34:54,626 --> 00:34:55,827
(children) Yes!

809
00:34:55,827 --> 00:34:58,330
You know, you can tell

810
00:34:58,330 --> 00:35:00,532
stories like that to each other.

811
00:35:00,532 --> 00:35:01,766
We don't know any.

812
00:35:01,766 --> 00:35:03,601
But you can read them.

813
00:35:03,601 --> 00:35:06,271
From books, you can read any

814
00:35:06,271 --> 00:35:07,739
story you want.

815
00:35:07,739 --> 00:35:09,507
We can't read.

816
00:35:09,507 --> 00:35:12,210
Ohh.

817
00:35:12,210 --> 00:35:14,346
Let me test you.

818
00:35:14,346 --> 00:35:17,282
Let's all together say the word

819
00:35:17,282 --> 00:35:18,283
"king."

820
00:35:18,283 --> 00:35:19,217
(children) King.

821
00:35:19,217 --> 00:35:20,318
Now, I show you how

822
00:35:20,318 --> 00:35:21,886
to write it.

823
00:35:24,522 --> 00:35:26,825
Kh-- everyone, "kh."

824
00:35:26,825 --> 00:35:27,759
(children repeat)

825
00:35:27,759 --> 00:35:29,828
Then, "ih."

826
00:35:29,828 --> 00:35:30,862
(children repeat)

827
00:35:30,862 --> 00:35:33,598
Then, "nnn."

828
00:35:33,598 --> 00:35:36,201
(children repeat)

829
00:35:36,201 --> 00:35:38,770
Then, "guh."

830
00:35:38,770 --> 00:35:39,871
(children repeat)

831
00:35:39,871 --> 00:35:42,474
And all together, that is...

832
00:35:42,474 --> 00:35:44,209
"Kh-ih-nnn-guh."

833
00:35:44,209 --> 00:35:45,310
(children) King!

834
00:35:45,310 --> 00:35:46,878
You see!

835
00:35:46,878 --> 00:35:48,580
You have just learned to read

836
00:35:48,580 --> 00:35:50,215
your first word!

837
00:35:50,215 --> 00:35:50,949
(gasps)

838
00:35:50,949 --> 00:35:52,517
Yay, we did it!

839
00:35:52,517 --> 00:35:54,586
(all clapping)

840
00:35:56,588 --> 00:35:57,822
"A."

841
00:35:57,822 --> 00:35:59,691
"N."

842
00:36:01,860 --> 00:36:04,829
"E." "N."

843
00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:05,764
(children repeating)

844
00:36:05,764 --> 00:36:08,333
"N," "N," "N."

845
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:09,768
"I."

846
00:36:09,768 --> 00:36:11,236
(children repeat)

847
00:36:11,236 --> 00:36:14,539
"N." E."

848
00:36:14,539 --> 00:36:15,707
(children repeat)

849
00:36:15,707 --> 00:36:17,442
Charu?

850
00:36:17,442 --> 00:36:19,544
"U." "N."

851
00:36:19,544 --> 00:36:21,246
Give this to the Sister.

852
00:36:21,246 --> 00:36:23,548
Go on.

853
00:36:23,548 --> 00:36:24,716
"Un."

854
00:36:24,716 --> 00:36:25,650
(children repeat)

855
00:36:25,650 --> 00:36:27,419
Oh!

856
00:36:31,723 --> 00:36:33,324
Beautiful.

857
00:36:33,324 --> 00:36:34,859
...lay them straight.

858
00:36:34,859 --> 00:36:37,696
Nine, ten...

859
00:36:37,696 --> 00:36:40,999
11, 12...

860
00:36:40,999 --> 00:36:43,968
13, 14...

861
00:36:43,968 --> 00:36:47,305
15, 16...

862
00:36:47,305 --> 00:36:50,708
17, 18...

863
00:36:50,708 --> 00:36:51,910
"L."

864
00:36:51,910 --> 00:36:53,378
(children repeat)

865
00:36:53,378 --> 00:36:54,612
"M."

866
00:36:54,612 --> 00:36:56,514
(children repeating)

867
00:37:00,418 --> 00:37:01,619
Why is she here?

868
00:37:01,619 --> 00:37:03,388
European woman, what does she

869
00:37:03,388 --> 00:37:04,355
want from us?

870
00:37:04,355 --> 00:37:05,523
She is teaching them about

871
00:37:05,523 --> 00:37:06,891
the Christian God.

872
00:37:06,891 --> 00:37:08,326
She wants to convert them

873
00:37:08,326 --> 00:37:09,294
to her faith.

874
00:37:09,294 --> 00:37:10,695
No, she's teaching them

875
00:37:10,695 --> 00:37:11,596
to read.

876
00:37:11,596 --> 00:37:12,597
She's giving them a chance

877
00:37:12,597 --> 00:37:13,465
in life.

878
00:37:13,465 --> 00:37:14,466
She's a troublemaker.

879
00:37:14,466 --> 00:37:15,467
You are a troublemaker,

