01:23:51,293 --> 01:23:53,362
Here, good man.

2024
01:23:53,362 --> 01:23:55,631
Friend.

2025
01:23:55,631 --> 01:23:56,598
Mother?

2026
01:23:56,598 --> 01:23:57,599
Oh!

2027
01:23:57,599 --> 01:23:58,367
I came to offer my

2028
01:23:58,367 --> 01:23:59,868
congratulations.

2029
01:23:59,868 --> 01:24:00,869
I won't be able to make

2030
01:24:00,869 --> 01:24:02,137
the ceremony.

2031
01:24:02,137 --> 01:24:03,205
Oh, I am only accepting for

2032
01:24:03,205 --> 01:24:04,840
the poor, Mr. Harper.

2033
01:24:04,840 --> 01:24:06,174
I'm only the instrument.

2034
01:24:06,174 --> 01:24:07,509
Yes, yes.

2035
01:24:07,509 --> 01:24:09,177
An international instrument

2036
01:24:09,177 --> 01:24:11,513
working in over 30 countries.

2037
01:24:11,513 --> 01:24:13,315
Ah, we are looking for new

2038
01:24:13,315 --> 01:24:15,117
recruits, if you are interested.

2039
01:24:15,117 --> 01:24:16,385
We have brothers working as

2040
01:24:16,385 --> 01:24:17,519
missionaries too, you know.

2041
01:24:17,519 --> 01:24:18,720
Oh, no, I'm too old

2042
01:24:18,720 --> 01:24:20,522
and too wise, Mother.

2043
01:24:20,522 --> 01:24:23,158
After what I've witnessed,

2044
01:24:23,158 --> 01:24:24,626
the depth of wretchedness,

2045
01:24:24,626 --> 01:24:26,662
extent of suffering,

2046
01:24:26,662 --> 01:24:28,530
it's everywhere.

2047
01:24:28,530 --> 01:24:29,531
But then I come here--

2048
01:24:29,531 --> 01:24:30,499
Mother, what happened to the

2049
01:24:30,499 --> 01:24:32,200
legacy of Gandhi?

2050
01:24:32,200 --> 01:24:33,602
I passed a statue on the way

2051
01:24:33,602 --> 01:24:34,536
here, it's surrounded by

2052
01:24:34,536 --> 01:24:36,772
soldiers and barbed wire.

2053
01:24:36,772 --> 01:24:38,340
They need guns to protect

2054
01:24:38,340 --> 01:24:39,741
a monument to a pacifist?

2055
01:24:39,741 --> 01:24:41,610
I mean, if a man like Gandhi

2056
01:24:41,610 --> 01:24:42,744
can't transform people--

2057
01:24:42,744 --> 01:24:44,880
Mr. Harper, come.

2058
01:24:44,880 --> 01:24:46,682
I want to show you something.

2059
01:24:46,682 --> 01:24:48,116
Come and see.

2060
01:24:52,187 --> 01:24:53,555
This is Dr. Rama.

2061
01:24:53,555 --> 01:24:54,823
He was a child

2062
01:24:54,823 --> 01:24:55,791
in a leper colony.

2063
01:24:55,791 --> 01:24:57,526
He got treatment because

2064
01:24:57,526 --> 01:24:59,895
we were able to reach him.

2065
01:24:59,895 --> 01:25:01,763
The money you raised for the

2066
01:25:01,763 --> 01:25:03,799
mobile clinic has changed the

2067
01:25:03,799 --> 01:25:04,900
lives of many more people

2068
01:25:04,900 --> 01:25:06,301
like him.

2069
01:25:06,301 --> 01:25:09,304
(sighs)

2070
01:25:09,304 --> 01:25:12,641
What is it?

2071
01:25:12,641 --> 01:25:14,476
Mother Teresa, what is it

2072
01:25:14,476 --> 01:25:15,644
that you expect to achieve

2073
01:25:15,644 --> 01:25:18,447
in your lifetime?

2074
01:25:18,447 --> 01:25:19,848
More.

2075
01:25:19,848 --> 01:25:21,483
More, more, always more.

2076
01:25:21,483 --> 01:25:23,485
But don't you see?

2077
01:25:23,485 --> 01:25:25,220
Your beloved poor, these--

2078
01:25:25,220 --> 01:25:25,921
these people that you call the

2079
01:25:25,921 --> 01:25:27,689
blessed ones, are the result of

2080
01:25:27,689 --> 01:25:29,958
a criminal failure of society.

2081
01:25:29,958 --> 01:25:31,460
Isn't it better to correct

2082
01:25:31,460 --> 01:25:33,228
the causes instead of treat

2083
01:25:33,228 --> 01:25:34,629
the symptoms?

2084
01:25:34,629 --> 01:25:35,564
Someone must comfort

2085
01:25:35,564 --> 01:25:37,466
the poor.

2086
01:25:37,466 --> 01:25:39,601
But that's the problem.

2087
01:25:39,601 --> 01:25:41,269
With all due respect,

2088
01:25:41,269 --> 01:25:42,604
Mother Teresa,

2089
01:25:42,604 --> 01:25:43,872
Nobel Peace Prizes do little

2090
01:25:43,872 --> 01:25:45,207
more than appease the conscience

2091
01:25:45,207 --> 01:25:46,642
of the world. We can all shed

2092
01:25:46,642 --> 01:25:48,910
a tear because someone like you

2093
01:25:48,910 --> 01:25:51,446
is taking care of the needy.

2094
01:25:51,446 --> 01:25:52,514
And then, when the speeches have

2095
01:25:52,514 --> 01:25:53,782
been made, we go right on

2096
01:25:53,782 --> 01:25:56,818
living our numb, ignorant lives.

2097
01:25:56,818 --> 01:25:58,754
Maybe our work will inspire

2098
01:25:58,754 --> 01:25:59,821
others who are better able

2099
01:25:59,821 --> 01:26:01,289
to change conditions.

2100
01:26:01,289 --> 01:26:02,457
Not if you continue to make

2101
01:26:02,457 --> 01:26:03,492
the poor into some kind of a

2102
01:26:03,492 --> 01:26:05,761
holy icon, Christ's body on

2103
01:26:05,761 --> 01:26:07,562
Earth-- they're not Christ!

2104
01:26:07,562 --> 01:26:08,897
What good is it to pretend

2105
01:26:08,897 --> 01:26:10,866
that they're saints?

2106
01:26:10,866 --> 01:26:12,834
We owe them everything.

2107
01:26:12,834 --> 01:26:14,970
You have Western mentality.

2108
01:26:14,970 --> 01:26:16,705
You expect too much

2109
01:26:16,705 --> 01:26:19,975
from poor humanity.

2110
01:26:19,975 --> 01:26:20,976
No, Mother, I--

2111
01:26:20,976 --> 01:26:22,544
I think you do.

2112
01:26:22,544 --> 01:26:26,481
You expect infinite forgiveness.

2113
01:26:26,481 --> 01:26:27,516
How can you forgive the

2114
01:26:27,516 --> 01:26:30,819
violence, the corruption?

2115
01:26:30,819 --> 01:26:32,354
Why don't you get angry?

2116
01:26:32,354 --> 01:26:33,655
I get angry, Mr. Harper,

2117
01:26:33,655 --> 01:26:35,657
I get angry often.

2118
01:26:35,657 --> 01:26:37,392
When I find an abandoned child,

2119
01:26:37,392 --> 01:26:38,927
I get angry.

2120
01:26:38,927 --> 01:26:40,362
I got angry when I first saw

2121
01:26:40,362 --> 01:26:41,530
Rama living in inhuman

2122
01:26:41,530 --> 01:26:42,731
conditions.

2123
01:26:42,731 --> 01:26:43,999
I get angry when I see young

2124
01:26:43,999 --> 01:26:45,867
girls brutalized and raped

2125
01:26:45,867 --> 01:26:47,702
during the wars.

2126
01:26:47,702 --> 01:26:49,671
I am angry.

2127
01:26:49,671 --> 01:26:51,840
But I have to forgive.

2128
01:26:51,840 --> 01:26:52,774
Otherwise, how can I do

2129
01:26:52,774 --> 01:26:54,476
the work?

2130
01:26:54,476 --> 01:26:57,546
I forgive, but I don't accept.

2131
01:27:02,350 --> 01:27:03,685
Well, I--

2132
01:27:03,685 --> 01:27:05,921
I don't understand, Mother.

2133
01:27:05,921 --> 01:27:08,723
I don't think I ever will.

2134
01:27:08,723 --> 01:27:09,891
Will you do one last thing

2135
01:27:09,891 --> 01:27:11,693
for me, Mr. Harper,

2136
01:27:11,693 --> 01:27:13,795
before you go?

2137
01:27:21,803 --> 01:27:23,572
(man speaking foreign language)

2138
01:27:23,572 --> 01:27:24,439
Come on, come on, come on,

2139
01:27:24,439 --> 01:27:27,075
come on.

2140
01:27:27,075 --> 01:27:30,378
(man continues speaking)

2141
01:27:30,378 --> 01:27:31,847
Excuse me, excuse me?

2142
01:27:31,847 --> 01:27:33,048
What-- what, uh--

2143
01:27:33,048 --> 01:27:36,384
what is he saying?

2144
01:27:36,384 --> 01:27:37,886
(speaks foreign language)

2145
01:27:40,856 --> 01:27:42,824
He's giving you his blessings.

2146
01:27:42,824 --> 01:27:46,528
He was blessing me?

2147
01:27:46,528 --> 01:27:47,395
Yes.

2148
01:27:47,395 --> 01:27:48,497
I could buy him a million

2149
01:27:48,497 --> 01:27:49,898
times over with the change

2150
01:27:49,898 --> 01:27:51,767
in my pocket.

2151
01:27:51,767 --> 01:27:53,635
Yes, but you couldn't

2152
01:27:53,635 --> 01:27:55,370
buy his blessing.

2153
01:28:10,785 --> 01:28:12,787
I never thought that I would,

2154
01:28:12,787 --> 01:28:14,723
uh...

2155
01:28:14,723 --> 01:28:16,825
when you cross that line.

2156
01:28:16,825 --> 01:28:17,959
If I had not picked up that

2157
01:28:17,959 --> 01:28:19,427
first person dying on the

2158
01:28:19,427 --> 01:28:21,029
streets, I never would have

2159
01:28:21,029 --> 01:28:22,864
picked up the thousands after.

2160
01:28:24,699 --> 01:28:26,735
(patting leg)

2161
01:28:39,614 --> 01:28:41,716
(applause)

2162
01:28:43,151 --> 01:28:45,453
Welcome, Mother Teresa.

2163
01:28:45,453 --> 01:28:46,755
On behalf of the Nobel

2164
01:28:46,755 --> 01:28:48,056
Peace Prize Committee

2165
01:28:48,056 --> 01:28:50,158
and the citizens of Oslo.

2166
01:28:50,158 --> 01:28:51,526
His Majesty, the King,

2167
01:28:51,526 --> 01:28:52,861
greets you and looks forward

2168
01:28:52,861 --> 01:28:53,829
to meeting you personally

2169
01:28:53,829 --> 01:28:56,631
at the ceremonial banquet.

2170
01:28:56,631 --> 01:28:57,866
Banquet?

2171
01:28:57,866 --> 01:29:00,569
Tomorrow night in your honor.

2172
01:29:00,569 --> 01:29:02,070
Oh, please,

2173
01:29:02,070 --> 01:29:03,805
have this banquet cancelled.

2174
01:29:03,805 --> 01:29:05,440
Cancelled?

2175
01:29:05,440 --> 01:29:06,808
Put aside the funds to feed

2176
01:29:06,808 --> 01:29:07,776
the hungry and the poor

2177
01:29:07,776 --> 01:29:08,977
in Calcutta.

2178
01:29:08,977 --> 01:29:10,078
There, it can provide hundreds

2179
01:29:10,078 --> 01:29:12,514
of meals for one whole year.

2180
01:29:12,514 --> 01:29:13,815
All right?

2181
01:29:13,815 --> 01:29:15,517
All right.

2182
01:29:15,517 --> 01:29:17,452
Hello, beautiful child.

2183
01:29:17,452 --> 01:29:19,588
God bless you.

2184
01:29:19,588 --> 01:29:21,590
Mother Teresa? Mother Teresa?

2185
01:29:21,590 --> 01:29:22,924
(overlapping chatter)

2186
01:29:22,924 --> 01:29:25,060
Bless you.

2187
01:29:25,060 --> 01:29:26,761
Bless you.

2188
01:29:28,997 --> 01:29:30,832
Bless you.

2189
01:29:32,934 --> 01:29:35,937
(applause)

2190
01:29:37,005 --> 01:29:39,174
I accept this award for the

2191
01:29:39,174 --> 01:29:41,643
glory of God,

2192
01:29:41,643 --> 01:29:42,611
and in the name

2193
01:29:42,611 --> 01:29:44,479
of the hungry,

2194
01:29:44,479 --> 01:29:46,715
of the naked,

2195
01:29:46,715 --> 01:29:49,217
of the homeless,

2196
01:29:49,217 --> 01:29:51,186
of the crippled,

2197
01:29:51,186 --> 01:29:52,787
the lepers,

2198
01:29:52,787 --> 01:29:55,190
and the blind.

2199
01:29:55,190 --> 01:29:56,691
In the name of all those

2200
01:29:56,691 --> 01:29:59,194
who feel unwanted,

2201
01:29:59,194 --> 01:30:00,829
unloved,

2202
01:30:00,829 --> 01:30:02,197
uncared for,

2203
01:30:02,197 --> 01:30:04,766
humiliated.

2204
01:30:04,766 --> 01:30:06,501
In their name, I accept

2205
01:30:06,501 --> 01:30:09,004
this award, because it will

2206
01:30:09,004 --> 01:30:12,107
bring an understanding love

2207
01:30:12,107 --> 01:30:15,844
between the rich and the poor.

2208
01:30:15,844 --> 01:30:18,146
Because all of us here,

2209
01:30:18,146 --> 01:30:20,749
we are proclaiming to the poor

2210
01:30:20,749 --> 01:30:22,651
that we love them,

2211
01:30:22,651 --> 01:30:25,186
that they too have been created,

2212
01:30:25,186 --> 01:30:28,123
by the loving hand of God,

2213
01:30:28,123 --> 01:30:31,126
to love and to be loved.

2214
01:30:32,794 --> 01:30:35,263
If we turn our back on the poor,

2215
01:30:35,263 --> 01:30:38,800
we are turning our back on God.

2216
01:30:38,800 --> 01:30:41,569
And at the hour of our death,

2217
01:30:41,569 --> 01:30:43,872
we shall be judged by what we

2218
01:30:43,872 --> 01:30:47,542
have done for and to the poor.

2219
01:30:49,144 --> 01:30:50,512
God bless you all.

2220
01:30:50,512 --> 01:30:53,615
(applause)

